## [2026-03-12] Bug Fix: EJS Layout Rendering Errors

**Type:** Bug Fix  
**Scope:** Medium - Template Rendering  
**Files Modified:** 16 files  
**Files Created:** 0 files  
**Lines Modified:** ~30 lines  
**Developer:** AI Assistant  
**Status:** ✅ Completed

### Overview
Fixed critical rendering errors preventing the application from starting. The issue was caused by incorrect `<% layout('layouts/main') %>` syntax in EJS template files, which is incompatible with express-ejs-layouts. Since the layout is configured globally in app.js, individual views should not call the layout function directly.

Additionally, updated error handling middleware to properly render error pages without attempting to use layouts, preventing circular dependency errors.

### Problem Description

**Initial Error:**
```
ReferenceError: layout is not defined
at views/error.ejs:1
```

**Root Cause:**
- All EJS view files contained `<% layout('layouts/main') %>` at the top
- This syntax is not valid for express-ejs-layouts
- express-ejs-layouts automatically applies the default layout set in app.js
- Views should only contain their content, not layout directives

**Secondary Issue:**
- Error pages were trying to use the layout system
- This caused circular dependency when errors occurred
- Error middleware needed to explicitly disable layouts when rendering error views

### Changes Made

#### 1. Removed Invalid Layout Calls from Views

**Files Modified (13 EJS view files):**

**Auth Views (4 files):**
- `views/auth/login.ejs` - Removed `<% layout('layouts/main') %>`
- `views/auth/register.ejs` - Removed `<% layout('layouts/main') %>`
- `views/auth/forgot-password.ejs` - Removed `<% layout('layouts/main') %>`
- `views/auth/reset-password.ejs` - Removed `<% layout('layouts/main') %>`

**Dashboard (1 file):**
- `views/dashboard/index.ejs` - Removed `<% layout('layouts/main') %>`

**Halls (3 files):**
- `views/halls/index.ejs` - Removed `<% layout('layouts/main') %>`
- `views/halls/create.ejs` - Removed `<% layout('layouts/main') %>`
- `views/halls/edit.ejs` - Removed `<% layout('layouts/main') %>`

**Movies (3 files):**
- `views/movies/index.ejs` - Removed `<% layout('layouts/main') %>`
- `views/movies/create.ejs` - Removed `<% layout('layouts/main') %>`
- `views/movies/edit.ejs` - Removed `<% layout('layouts/main') %>`

**Screenings (2 files):**
- `views/screenings/index.ejs` - Removed `<% layout('layouts/main') %>`
- `views/screenings/create.ejs` - Removed `<% layout('layouts/main') %>`

**Technical Details:**
Each file had the first line removed and leading whitespace adjusted. The views now start directly with their content.

#### 2. Fixed Error Page Rendering

**File Modified:** `views/error.ejs`
- Converted from layout-dependent to standalone HTML page
- Added complete HTML structure with head, body sections
- Included Bootstrap CSS/JS directly
- Now renders independently without requiring layout system
- Lines modified: Full file rewrite (~55 lines)

**Before:**
```ejs
<% layout('layouts/main') %>
<div class="row">
  <!-- error content -->
</div>
```

**After:**
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <!-- Full head with Bootstrap -->
</head>
<body>
  <!-- Standalone error page -->
</body>
</html>
```

#### 3. Updated Error Middleware to Disable Layouts

**File Modified:** `middleware/errorMiddleware.js`
- Added `layout: false` parameter to all error render calls (5 locations)
- Prevents express-ejs-layouts from attempting to wrap error views
- Lines modified: ~10 lines

**Locations Updated:**
1. Mongoose validation error handler
2. Mongoose duplicate key error handler (11000)
3. Mongoose cast error handler
4. Operational error handler (AppError)
5. Generic error handler (500)

**Code Pattern:**
```javascript
// Before
res.status(400).render('error', {
    title: 'Error',
    message: 'Error message',
    user: res.locals.user
});

// After
res.status(400).render('error', {
    title: 'Error',
    message: 'Error message',
    user: res.locals.user,
    layout: false  // ← Added
});
```

#### 4. Fixed Auth Middleware Error Rendering

**File Modified:** `middleware/authMiddleware.js`
- Added `layout: false` to error renders in access control (2 locations)
- Affects `requireAdmin` and `requireRole` middleware
- Lines modified: ~4 lines

